oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of WWI soldiers on board troopship
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Entitled "Sea Sick," photograph shows a group of soldiers in some discomfort on board a troopship, possibly the USS Powhatan. They appear to be wearing demium work uniforms with raincoats and overseas caps. The Still Image is associated with Horace Collins. Sgt. Horace E. Collins served in Co. E, 105th Supply Train, 55th Depot Brigade. Collins was from St. Elmo in Hamilton County, Tennessee.
